Pre-Game Insights: Sweden and Azerbaijan will play a pivotal match for the UEFA Nations League, League C, Group 1 on September 5, 2024.
The competition will take place in the 31,200-seat Tofiq Bahramov Republican Stadium in Baku, Azerbaijan.
The start time of the match is 16:00 UTC.
Berke B., a Hungarian referee with expertise and authority, will officiate the game.
Group 1 is currently being led by Azerbaijan, with Sweden in fourth position.
Both clubs need to win this game in order to maintain their group standing, pursue promotions, and avoid relegation.
Azerbaijan’s recent performance has been inconsistent, which may have an impact on how they play against Sweden.
Sweden has also experienced a series of mixed outcomes in their recent fixtures.
Sweden has a strong head-to-head record against Azerbaijan, suggesting that team has performed well in previous meetings.
Sweden has won four of the previous five games against Azerbaijan, maintaining their historical dominance.
Azerbaijan emerged victorious in their most recent meeting in November 2023.

Azerbaijan’s probable lineup includes Mahammadaliyev (GK), Mammadov (DF), Mustafazada (DF), Kryvotsiuk (DF), Cafarquliyev (DF), Sheydayev (MF), Isayev (MF), Diniyev (MF), Bayramov (MF), Mahmudov (FW), Dadashov (FW).
Sweden’s probable lineup includes Olsen (GK), Wahlqvist (DF), Lindelof (DF), Helander (DF), Sema (DF), Svanberg (MF), Cajuste (MF), Gustafson (MF), Forsberg (MF), Gyokeres (FW), Kulusevski (FW).
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game’s outcome could be significantly impacted by the state of the field at Tofiq Bahramov Republican Stadium and the Baku climate.
Sweden might be more vulnerable to rain and other bad weather that could hinder player footing and ball movement than Azerbaijan because they are not used to these situations.
